
[1]pantomime

   PAN'TOMIME, n. [L. pantomimus; Gr. all, and a mimic.]

   1. One that imitates all sorts of actions and characters without
   speaking; one that expresses his meaning by mute action. The pantomimes
   of antiquity used to express in gestures and action, whatever the
   chorus sung, changing their countenance and behavior as the subject of
   the song varied.

   2. A scene or representation in dumb show.

   3. A species of musical entertainment.

              PAN'TOMIME, a. Representing only in mute action.
